
[1]singleness

   SIN'GLENESS, n.

   1. The state of being one only or separate from all others; the
   opposite of doubleness, complication or multiplicity.

   2. Simplicity; sincerity; purity of mind or purpose; freedom from
   duplicity; as singleness of belief; singleness of heart.
